2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper aims to deploy the object recognition resource in a robotic application, indicating a strong connection to robotics.
3. cs.AR (Augmented Reality): The use of object recognition in robotics can also be applied to augmented reality, making this sub-category a likely fit.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The FPGA-based implementation involves hardware design and control, which falls under this sub-category.
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The use of DCNNs for object recognition is a machine learning technique, making this sub-category a possible fit as well.
